‚úÖ Steps to Set Up Automatic EC2 Backup Using AWS Backup
1Ô∏è‚É£ Open AWS Backup
Go to AWS Console ‚Üí Search and open AWS Backup.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Backup Vault (Optional)
Navigate to Backup Vaults ‚Üí Click Create Backup Vault.

Name: MyEC2BackupVault

(Optional) Add tags or encryption settings.

Click Create backup vault.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Backup Plan
Go to Backup plans ‚Üí Click Create Backup Plan.

Choose Build a new plan.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Define Backup Rule
Name: DailyEC2Backup

Backup frequency: Choose from dropdown:

Every 12 hours

Daily

Weekly

Monthly

Backup window: Choose preferred time range (default is OK).

Lifecycle settings:

Transition to cold storage: (Optional)

Expire after: e.g., 7 days (delete old backups)

5Ô∏è‚É£ Assign Backup Vault
Choose the vault: MyEC2BackupVault

6Ô∏è‚É£ Assign Resources
After plan is created ‚Üí Click Assign Resources

Select EC2 resource type

Assign using:

Resource ID (Instance ID), or

Tag-based selection (e.g., Key=Backup, Value=Daily)

